  "rationale": "<p>The correct answer is 23. Since it&rsquo;s given that <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"x equals 2\"></span>, the value of <span class=\"italic\">y</span> can be found by substituting 2 for <span class=\"italic\">x</span> in the first equation and solving for <span class=\"italic\">y</span>. Substituting 2 for <span class=\"italic\">x</span> yields <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"3 times 2, plus y, equals 29\"></span>, or <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"6 plus y, equals 29\"></span>. Subtracting 6 from both sides of this equation yields <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"y equals 23\"></span>.</p>\n",
